21/12/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Wrapping up a visit to BiH on Monday (20 December), EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn said co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal and reforming the police remain the main conditions for starting talks between BiH and the EU on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA).
Following talks with the tripartite presidency and BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic, Rehn also called on politicians to ensure stability and guarantee the timely and successful implementation of EU-related reforms.
In other news, Bosnian Serb General Radislav Krstic, the first person to be convicted of genocide by the UN war crimes tribunal, has been transferred to Britain to serve his 35-year prison sentence.
He led the Serb attack on Srebrenica in July 1995.
(Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 21/12/04;
PBS BiH, Fena, RTRS - 20/12/04)
